VIDEO ON SNAP MAP INDICATED SIGNIFICANT, WIDESPREAD STREET FLOODING WITH AT LEAST A COUPLE FEET OF WATER OVER STREETS AND SURROUNDING PROPERTY -- IN THE VICINITY OF THE INTERSECTION OF SOUTH 9TH STREET AND SOUTH 5TH AVENUE.

DELAYED REPORT: SPORTS UTILITY VEHICLE LARGELY SUBMERGED INTO A STORM-DRAIN RUNOFF AREA THAT EMPTIES INTO WEST LAKE IN DOWNTOWN NAPLES. WATERS POOLED TO AROUND A FEW FEET WITHIN THE STORM-DRAIN RUNOFF AREA FROM EARLIER HEAVY RAINS AND FLASH FLOODING IN NAPLES, AND APPEARED TO BE VISUALLY INDISTINGUISHABLE FROM SIGNIFICANTLY FLOODED STREETS IN THE DOWNTOWN NAPLES AREA. THIS REPORT WAS PROVIDED BY THE NAPLES FIRE-RESCUE DEPARTMENT, ALSO RELAYED BY BROADCAST MEDIA.
